{"metadata": {"team_id": "strip", "topic_id": "1001", "run_id": "strip-opportunity", "task": "english"}, "responses": [{"text": "This report addresses: Geoffrey Hinton's AI Concerns", "citations": {}}, {"text": "These are the 4 jobs that are set to disappear in a decade, and the ones that will take over\n\nMay 6, 2023, 10:00 AM UTC\nA fax machine was memorably dispatched in the classic workplace comedy \"Office Space.\"\nGetty Images\n\nIf you\u2019re concerned about ChatGPT and artificial intelligence snapping up your job, you\u2019re far from the only one.", "citations": {"d490c53b-a3c0-4442-9a80-1a11110c988f_633609416": 17.0}}, {"text": "\u201cHow do we survive that?\u201d Hinton asks.}\n\nThe WEF argues what\u2019s becoming quite clear: Time is running out now for millions of roles, especially those trying to resist digital transformation, before they go the way of the fax machine.", "citations": {"d490c53b-a3c0-4442-9a80-1a11110c988f_633609416": 12.0}}, {"text": "Throughout his career, Yoshua\u2019s research has been instrumental in shaping the world\u2019s understanding of AI\u2019s potential\u2014and that same expertise has made his perspective more essential than ever.", "citations": {"09887dcf-8df7-4f1e-b60b-875b3d1bd775_245465706": 13.0}}, {"text": "Yoshua has been concerned for many years with the social impact of artificial intelligence, contributing to the Montreal Declaration for the Responsible Development of AI.", "citations": {"09887dcf-8df7-4f1e-b60b-875b3d1bd775_245465706": 10.0}}, {"text": "Google seeks to fix fairness in AI technology\n\nBy Tara Deschamps, The Canadian Press, Toronto\u00a0 \u00a0\n\nAutomation / Robotics Electronics AI artificial intelligence Google Technology\n\nBut artificial intelligence still has biases echoed by society\n\nAn artificial intelligence researcher at Google says fixing fairness in the technology \u201cisn\u2019t a simple thing,\u201d but the world has an opportunity to get it right as the software explodes in popularity.", "citations": {"ecdf4a88-257b-447c-97d4-af3263c416a5_302105403": 20.0}}, {"text": "Advertisement\n\nGeoffrey Hinton, the British-Canadian computer scientist widely considered the `godfather of AI\u2019, is so concerned with the technology he left Google so he can more freely discuss the dangers, which he has said include bias and discrimination, joblessness, echo chambers, fake news, battle robots and existential risk.", "citations": {"ecdf4a88-257b-447c-97d4-af3263c416a5_302105403": 16.0}}], "references": ["d490c53b-a3c0-4442-9a80-1a11110c988f_633609416", "09887dcf-8df7-4f1e-b60b-875b3d1bd775_245465706", "ecdf4a88-257b-447c-97d4-af3263c416a5_302105403"]}
