opularity.", "citations": {"ecdf4a88-257b-447c-97d4-af3263c416a5_302105403": 20.0}}, {"text": "Advertisement\n\nGeoffrey Hinton, the British-Canadian computer scientist widely considered the `godfather of AI\u2019, is so concerned with the technology he left Google so he can more freely discuss the dangers, which he has said include bias and discrimination, joblessness, echo chambers, fake news, battle robots and existential risk.", "citations": {"ecdf4a88-257b-447c-97d4-af3263c416a5_302105403": 16.0}}], "references": ["d490c53b-a3c0-4442-9a80-1a11110c988f_633609416", "09887dcf-8df7-4f1e-b60b-875b3d1bd775_245465706", "ecdf4a88-257b-447c-97d4-af3263c416a5_302105403"]}
{"metadata": {"team_id": "strip", "topic_id": "1003", "run_id": "strip-opportunity", "task": "english"}, "responses": [{"text": "This report addresses: Digital Nomads", "citations": {}}, {"text": "\"As part of the onboarding process for each new member, we try to understand who they are and what they're trying to achieve, and the community at each of our facilities is great at helping people to meet new people, learn how the system works, and so on.\"\n\nHSBC has attempted to tap into the experience of these frequent movers as part of its Unforeign Exchange campaign, with a wide range of people who move frequently for work and pleasure providing tips on how they have managed to make the process a success.", "citations": {"b9c518dd-990c-4c58-be79-2c42cfc37da2_142781026": 29.0}}, {"text": "\"Home is a psychological state as much as a physical place, defined by a sense of belonging \u2013 a feeling of being an accepted part of a larger community.\"\n\nAmong the various suggestions Cohen makes, most revolve around the power of community, both to provide people with a support network to help during the transition but also to help to understand and integrate with the local community.", "citations": {"b9c518dd-990c-4c58-be79-2c42cfc37da2_142781026": 18.0}}, {"text": "Spain leads the way\n\nFor UK nationals seeking relocation for a better quality of life, one country stands out as the preferred destination for remote work, with 22 per cent choosing Spain as their first option\n\nThe United States received 19 per cent of the votes and France in third place with 13 per cent.", "citations": {"371fe2ab-8293-426e-922b-27ca7935f5dd_79937127": 12.0}}, {"text": "With 46 per cent of British professionals considering relocating for remote work, the survey sheds light on this trend.", "citations": {"371fe2ab-8293-426e-922b-27ca7935f5dd_79937127": 7.0}}, {"text": "These guys in the Russian IT community do not watch TV or listen to the state radio, preferring to get their information from internet channels and hence have a clearer picture of what is happening in Ukraine.", "citations": {"7dacd76e-1af8-42d2-82fa-ff9963d06419_294583483": 11.0}}, {"text": "This is only a first wave, says the association, which expects up to 100,000 additional IT workers to leave in April.", "citations": {"7dacd76e-1af8-42d2-82fa-ff9963d06419_294583483": 7.0}}], "references": ["b9c518dd-990c-4c58-be79-2c42cfc37da2_142781026", "371fe2ab-8293-426e-922b-27ca7935f5dd_79937127", "7dacd76e-1af8-42d2-82fa-ff9963d06419_294583483"]}
{"metadata": {"team_id": "strip", "topic_id": "1004", "run_id": "strip-opportunity", "task": "english"}, "responses": [{"text": "This report addresses: Digital Nomads", "citations": {}}, {"text": "\"As part of the onboarding process for each new member, we try to understand who they are and what they're trying to achieve, and the community at each of our facilities is great at helping people to meet new people, learn how the system works, and so on.\"\n\nHSBC has attempted to tap into the experience of these frequent movers as part of its Unforeign Exchange campaign, with a wide range of people who move frequently for work and pleasure providing tips on how they have managed to make the process a success.", "citations": {"b9c518dd-990c-4c58-be79-2c42cfc37da2_142781026": 29.0}}, {"text": "\"Home is a psychological state as much as a physical place, defined by a sense of belonging \u2013 a feeling of being an accepted part of a larger community.\"\n\nAmong the various suggestions Cohen makes, most revolve around the power of community, both to provide people with a support network to help during the transition but also to help to understand and integrate with the local community.", "citations": {"b9c518dd-990c-4c58-be79-2c42cfc37da2_142781026": 18.0}}, {"text": "Spain leads the way\n\nFor UK nationals seeking relocation for a better quality of life, one country stands out as the preferred destination for remote work, with 22 per cent choosing Spain as their first option\n\nThe United States received 19 per cent of the votes and France in third place with 13 per cent.", "citations": {"371fe2ab-8293-426e-922b-27ca7935f5dd_79937127": 12.0}}, {"text": "With 46 per cent of British professionals considering relocating for remote work, the survey sheds light on this trend.", "citations": {"371fe2ab-8293-426e-922b-27ca7935f5dd_79937127": 7.0}}, {"text": "These guys in the Russian IT community do not watch TV or listen to the state radio, preferring to get their information from internet channels and hence have a clearer picture of what is happening in Ukraine.", "citations": {"7dacd76e-1af8-42d2-82fa-ff9963d06419_294583483": 11.0}}, {"text": "This is only a first wave, says the association, which expects up to 100,000 additional IT workers to leave in April.", "citations": {"7dacd76e-1af8-42d2-82fa-ff9963d06419_294583483": 7.0}}], "references": ["b9c518dd-990c-4c58-be79-2c42cfc37da2_142781026", "371fe2ab-8293-426e-922b-27ca7935f5dd_79937127", "7dacd76e-1af8-42d2-82fa-ff9963d06419_294583483"]}
{"metadata": {"team_id": "strip", "topic_id": "1005", "run_id": "strip-opportunity", "task": "english"}, "responses": [{"text": "This report addresses: Digital Nomads", "citations": {}}, {"text": "Mobile office essentials\n\nAmazon \u00a0\n\nThe onset of the Covid-19 pandemic all but accelerated the transition to the remote work lifestyle, and now that the pandemic has just about subsided, most of us have become used to the work-from-home routine.", "citations": {"23980c8b-8970-4b9b-96ce-6f690a62ec45_787468909": 17.0}}, {"text": "As a matter of fact, many full-time work-from-home professionals have grown to love this way of life since it affords them more time with family members and an opportunity to travel while they work.", "citations": {"23980c8b-8970-4b9b-96ce-6f690a62ec45_787468909": 14.0}}, {"text": "The Brazilian Agency for International Tourism Promotion, Embratur, announced that it would partner with the Portuguese company NomadX to stimulate the creation of coworking focused on foreigners who want to travel to Brazil and work remotely at the same time (the so-called \"digital nomads\").", "citations": {"d812d020-b4d6-4b3b-a420-9f195bdf4ac4_35559448": 17.0}}, {"text": "It is estimated that there are 35 million digital nomads worldwide, i.e., people who combine remote work and travel between countries and continents for various periods.", "citations": {"d812d020-b4d6-4b3b-a420-9f195bdf4ac4_35559448": 12.0}}, {"text": "OPEN APP\nHome / Markets / Cryptocurrency /\u00a0 Crypto nomads move back to big cities like London, New York in bear market\n\nCrypto nomads move back to big cities like London, New York in bear market\n\nThe nomadic life is especially well suited to the crypto crowd, with its 24/7 market and ethos of a digital, borderless monetary future, but pandemic travel restrictions, followed by a crash in cryptocurrency prices have made it less practical and too expensive of a lifestyle to maintain\n\nListen to this article\n\nOver the years, Oliver Gale\u2019s workplace view has included the palm-lined promenade of Miami Beach, the sandy shores of Barbados and the turquoise waters of Mexico\u2019s Caribbean coast.", "citations": {"d6326b30-5d72-4c6e-8a2c-7bcc09d1089b_361148253": 29.0}}, {"text": "\u201cWith crypto integrating into more aspects of traditional businesses and industries -- being in a major city like New York or London is beneficial from a networking standpoint as well.\"\n\nGale, who is also the co-founder and CEO of blockchain project Panther Protocol, returned to London in March 2020 to start Elemental.io, a consumer credit platform formerly known a", "citations": {"d6326b30-5d72-4c6e-8a2c-7bcc09d1089b_361148253": 12.0}}], "references": ["23980c8b-8970-4b9b-96ce-6f690a62ec45_787468909", "d812d020-b4d6-4b3b-a420-9f195bdf4ac4_35559448", "d6326b30-5d72-4c6e-8a2c-7bcc09d1089b_361148253"]}
{"metadata": {"team_id": "strip", "topic_id": "1006", "run_id": "strip-opportunity", "task": "english"}, "responses": [{"text": "This report addresses: Digital Nomads", "citations": {}}, {"text": "Mobile office essentials\n\nAmazon \u00a0\n\nThe onset of the Covid-19 pandemic all but accelerated the transition to the remote work lifestyle, and now that the pandemic has just about subsided, most of us have become used to the work-from-home routine.", "citations": {"23980c8b-8970-4b9b-96ce-6f690a62ec45_787468909": 17.0}}, {"text": "As a matter of fact, many full-time work-from-home professionals have grown to love this way of life since it affords them more time with family members and an opportunity to travel while they work.", "citations": {"23980c8b-8970-4b9b-96ce-6f690a62ec45_787468909": 14.0}}, {"text": "The Brazilian Agency for International Tourism Promotion, Embratur, announced that it would partner with the Portuguese company NomadX to stimulate the creation of coworking focused on foreigners who want to travel to Brazil and work remotely at the same time (the so-called \"digital nomads\").", "citations": {"d812d020-b4d6-4b3b-a420-9f195bdf4ac4_35559448": 17.0}}, {"text": "It is estimated that there are 35 million digital nomads worldwide, i.e., people who combine remote work and travel between countries and continents for various periods.", "citations": {"d812d020-b4d6-4b3b-a420-9f195bdf4ac4_35559448": 12.0}}, {"text": "OPEN APP\nHome / Markets / Cryptocurrency /\u00a0 Crypto nomads move back to big cities like London, New York in bear market\n\nCrypto nomads move back to big cities like London, New York in bear market\n\nThe nomadic life is especially well suited to the crypto crowd, with its 24/7 market and ethos of a digital, borderless monetary future, but pandemic travel restrictions, followed by a crash in cryptocurrency prices have made it less practical and too expensive of a lifestyle to maintain\n\nListen to this article\n\nOver the years, Oliver Gale\u2019s workplace view has included the palm-lined promenade of Miami Beach, the sandy shores of Barbados and the turquoise waters of Mexico\u2019s Caribbean coast.", "citations": {"d6326b30-5d72-4c6e-8a2c-7bcc09d1089b_361148253": 29.0}}, {"text": "\u201cWith crypto integrating into more aspects of traditional businesses and industries -- being in a major city like New York or London is beneficial from a networking standpoint as well.\"\n\nGale, who is also the co-founder and CEO of blockchain project Panther Protocol, returned to London in March 2020 to start Elemental.io, a consumer credit platform formerly known as PayMachine.", "citations": {"d6326b30-5d72-4c6e-8a2c-7bcc09d1089b_361148253": 12.0}}], "references": ["23980c8b-8970-4b9b-96ce-6f690a62ec45_787468909", "d812d020-b4d6-4b3b-a420-9f195bdf4ac4_35559448", "d6326b30-5d72-4c6e-8a2c-7bcc09d1089b_361148253"]}
